<ul class="definition" data-word = 'Copernican Principle'>
    <li>
        There are no special observers in the universe.
    </li>
    <li>
        Humans are not situated at the center or at any special point in the universe.
    </li>
    <li>
        Someone in a galaxy 1 billion light years away, when observing the universe,
        would see something similar to what we see.
    </li>
</ul>


