<ul class="definition" data-word = 'Ptolemaic Model'>
    <li>
        The earth is situated at the center of the universe.
    </li>
    <li>
        The moon, sun, stars, and all planets orbit the earth.
    </li>
    <li>
        The retrograde motion of the planets occur because the
        they move in circles inside of circles.
    </li>
</ul>

<ul class="definition" data-word = 'Copernican Model'>
    <li>
        The sun is situated at the center (of the universe that was known at that time.)
    </li>
    <li>
        Earth is grouped with the planets. All planets orbit the sun in circles
    </li>
</ul>

<p>
    Note that the Copernican model is <emph>not perfect</emph>.
    For one thing, later astronomers discovered planets move in ellipses, not circles.
    However, not physical model is perfect: the important thing is that newer,
    models that match data better with simpler assumptions are being developed.
</p>